es]]\n* [[Mariza]]\n* [[Carlos do Carmo]]\n* [[Carlos Paredes]]\n* [[Zeca Afonso]]\n\n== People ==\n* [[Ant\u00f3nio Guterres]]\n* [[Jos\u00e9 Manuel Barroso]]\n* [[M\u00e1rio Centeno]]\n* [[Sara Sampaio]]\n* [[Maria Helena Vieira da Silva]]\n* [[Paula Rego]]\n* [[\u00c1lvaro Siza Vieira]]\n* [[Eduardo Souto de Moura]]\n* [[Calouste Gulbenkian]]\n* [[M\u00e1rio Soares]]\n* [[Joana Vasconcelos]]\n* [[F\u00e1tima Lopes]]\n\n== Places ==\n* [[Lisbon]]\n* [[Porto]]\n* [[Algarve]]\n* [[Madeira]]\n* [[Azores]]\n* [[Alentejo]]\n* [[Coimbra]]\n* [[Tr\u00e1s-os-Montes (region)|Tr\u00e1s-os-Montes]]\n* [[Minho Province|Minho]] / [[Entre-Douro-e-Minho Province|Entre-Douro-e-Minho]] \n* [[Ribatejo Province|Ribatejo]]\n* [[Beira (Portugal)|Beira]] / [[Beira Litoral Province|Beira Litoral]] / [[Beira Interior]] [[Beira Alta Province|Beira Alta]] / [[Beira Baixa Province|Beira Baixa]]\n* [[Peneda-Ger\u00eas National Park]]\n* [[List of beaches in Portugal|Portuguese beaches]]\n\n== Sport ==\n* [[Cristiano Ronaldo]]\n* [[Eus\u00e9bio]]\n* [[Jos\u00e9 Mourinho]]\n* [[Lu\u00eds Figo]]\n* [[Pauleta]]\n* [[Primeira Liga]]\n* [[S.L. Benfica]]\n* [[FC Porto]]\n* [[Sporting CP]]\n* [[Rosa Mota]]\n* [[Carlos Lopes]]\n\n== Television, film and theatre ==\n* [[Carmen Miranda]]\n* [[Manoel de Oliveira]]\n* [[Beatriz Costa]]\n* [[Vasco Santana]]\n* [[Ant\u00f3nio Silva (actor)|Ant\u00f3nio Silva]]\n* [[Joaquim de Almeida]]\n* [[Daniela Ruah]]\n* [[Herman Jos\u00e9]]\n* [[Ricardo Ara\u00fajo Pereira]]\n* [[A Can\u00e7\u00e3o de Lisboa]]\n\n==See also==\n* [[Cultural icon]]\n* [[Culture of Portugal]]\n\n{{Portugal topics}}\n\n[[Category:Portuguese culture]]\n[[Category:Lists of cultural icons|Portugal]]\n[[Category:Cultural history of Portugal]]\n", "text_old": "{{short description|Wikipedia list article}}\n[[File:Flag of Portugal.svg|thumb|right|Flag of Portugal]]\n[[File:Viriato.JPG|thumb|right|[[Viriato]]]]\n[[File:Nuno Gon\u00e7alves. Paineis de S\u00e3o Vicente de Fora.jpg|thumb|right|''[[Saint Vincent Panels]]'' by [[Nuno Gon\u00e7alves]]]]\n[[File:Jer\u00f3nimos April 2009-4.jpg|thumb|right|[[Jer\u00f3nimos Monastery]]]]\n[[File:Castelo de Guimar\u00e3es Castelo da Funda\u00e7\u00e3o.JPG|thumb|right|[[Guimar\u00e3es Castle]]]]\n[[File:Torre Belem (Lisboa).jpg|right|thumb|[[Torre de Bel\u00e9m]]]]\n[[File:Forcado numa Pega de Caras no Campo Pequeno.jpg|thumb|right|[[Forcado]] in a [[bullring]]]]\n[[File:Jose malhoa fado.jpg|right|thumb|[[Fado]] (''O Fado'' by [[Jos\u00e9 Malhoa]])]]\n[[File:Vasco da Gama - 1838.png|thumb|right|[[Vasco da Gama]]]]\n[[File:Maria Helena Vieira da Silva - Self-portrait.jpg|thumb|right|[[Maria Helena Vieira da Silva|Vieira da Silva]]]]\n[[File:Saramago, Jos\u00e9 (1922)-2.jpg|right|thumb|[[Jos\u00e9 Saramago]]]]\n[[File:Zepovinho.jpg|right|thumb|[[Z\u00e9 Povinho]]]]\n[[File:Os Lus\u00edadas.jpg|right|thumb|[[Cam\u00f5es]]' ''[[Os Lus\u00edadas]]'']]\n[[File:Cristiano Ronaldo 2018.jpg|thumb|right|[[Cristiano Ronaldo]]]]\n[[File:Portugal national football team World Cup 2018.jpg|thumb|right|[[Portugal national football team]]]]\n[[File:Bacalao (5480339132).jpg|right|thumb|[[Bacalao]]]]\n[[File:Past\u00e9is de Bel\u00e9m.JPG|right|thumb|''[[Past\u00e9is de nata]]'' or ''past\u00e9is de Bel\u00e9m'' (cream custards)]]\n[[File:Port wine.jpg|right|thumb|[[Port wine]]]]\n\nThis '''List of cultural icons of Portugal''' is a list of links to potential [[cultural icon]]s of [[Portugal]].\n\n== Art and craft ==\n* [[Azulejo]]\n* [[Portuguese pavement]]\n* [[Portuguese faience]]\n* [[Portuguese filigree]]\n* [[Arraiolos rug]]\n* [[Madeira embroidery]]\n* [[Portuguese cowbell]]\n* [[Madeira wickerwork]]\n* [[Madeira marqueterie]]\n\n== Buildings ==\n* [[Pra\u00e7a do Com\u00e9rcio]]\n* [[Rossio]]\n* [[D. Maria II National Theatre]]\n* [[Rossio railway station]]\n* [[Lisbon City Hall]]\n* [[Porto City Hall]]\n* [[Casa da M\u00fasica]]\n* [[Bel\u00e9m Cultural Center]]\n* [[Casa das Hist\u00f3rias Paula Rego]]\n* [[Serralves]]\n* [[Calouste Gulbenkian Foundation]]\n* [[Museum of Art, Architecture and Technology]]\n* [[Pavilion of Portugal]]\n* [[Pena Palace]]\n* [[Castle of Guimar\u00e3es]]\n* [[Castle of \u00d3bidos]]\n*[[Caf\u00e9 A Brasileira]]\n* [[Bel\u00e9m Tower]]\n* [[Cl\u00e9rigos Church]]\n* [[S\u00e3o Bento Railway Station]]\n* [[Jer\u00f3nimos Monastery]]\n* [[S\u00e3o Jorge Castle]]\n* [[Palace of Mafra]]\n* [[Alcoba\u00e7a Monastery]]\n* [[Batalha Monastery]]\n* [[Bel\u00e9m Palace]]\n* [[S\u00e3o Bento Palace]]\n* [[Palace of Ajuda]]\n* [[Palace of Queluz]]\n* [[Carmo Convent]]\n* [[Mateus Palace]]\n* [[Gare do Oriente]]\n* [[Vasco da Gama Bridge]]\n* [[25 de Abril Bridge]]\n* [[Dom Lu\u00eds I Bridge]]\n* [[Quinta da Regaleira]]\n* [[Sintra National Palace]]\n* [[Livraria Lello]]\n* \n\n<br />\n== Emblems and symbols ==\n\n* [[Flag of Portugal]]\n* [[Coat of arms of Portugal]]\n* [[A Portuguesa]], the national anthem\n* [[Rooster of Barcelos]]\n\n== Festivals ==\n* [[Midsummer|Santos Populares]] (Popular Saints celebrations)\n* [[Madeira Flower Festival]]\n\n== Food and drinks ==\n\n* [[Pastel de nata]]\n* [[Bacalhau]]\n* [[Cozido \u00e0 portuguesa]]\n* [[Feijoada|Feijoada \u00e0 portuguesa]]\n* [[Caldo verde]]\n* [[Sardine]]\n* [[Alheira]]\n* [[Francesinha]]\n* [[Gaspacho]]\n* [[Port wine]]\n* [[Madeira wine]]\n* [[Ginjinha]]\n\n== Government ==\n* [[Marcelo Rebelo de Sousa]]\n* [[Ant\u00f3nio Costa]]\n* [[Eduardo Ferro Rodrigues]]\n* [[Assembly of the Republic (Portugal)|Assembly of the Republic]]\n* [[President of Portugal]]\n* [[Prime Minister of Portugal]]\n* [[Constitutional Court (Portugal)|Constitutional Court]]\n* [[Supreme Court (Portugal)|Supreme Court]]\n\n== History and legend ==\n* [[Viriathus]]\n* [[V\u00edmara Peres]]\n* [[Padeira de Aljubarrota]]\n* [[Afonso I of Portugal]]\n* [[Nuno \u00c1lvares Pereira]]\n* [[Vasco da Gama]]\n* [[Ferdinand Magellan]]\n* [[Prince Henry the Navigator]]\n* [[Pedro \u00c1lvares Cabral]]\n\n== Holidays ==\n* [[Freedom Day (Portugal)|