ily Telegraph]] |date=8 March 1999 |url=https://www.telegraph.co.uk/news/obituaries/culture-obituaries/film-obituaries/7367562/Stanley-Kubrick.html}}</ref>\n| 1928\n| 1999\n| American film director \n|-\n| [[Harper Lee]]<ref name=Observer>{{cite news |title=Mockingbird author steps out of shadows |author=Paul Harris |newspaper=[[The Observer]] |date=5 February 2006 |url=https://www.theguardian.com/world/2006/feb/05/books.usa |location=London}}</ref> \n| 1926\n| 2016\n| Author of ''[[To Kill a Mockingbird]]''\n|-\n| [[Terrence Malick]]<ref>{{cite news |title=The Not-So-Secret Life of Terrence Malick|author=Eric Benson |magazine=[[Texas Monthly]] |date=April 2017 | url=https://www.texasmonthly.com/the-culture/the-not-so-secret-life-of-terrence-malick/location=Texas}}|</ref> \n| 1943\n| \n| American film director \n|-\n| [[Cormac McCarthy]]<ref>{{cite news |url=https://www.nytimes.com/1992/04/19/books/cormac-mccarthys-venomous-fiction.html |title=Cormac McCarthy's Venomous Fiction |author=Richard B. Woodward |date=19 April 1992 |newspaper=The New York Times}}</ref><ref>{{cite news |title=The late Harper Lee and five other reclusive authors |author=Martin Chilton |newspaper=[[The Daily Telegraph|The Telegraph]] |date=19 February 2016 |url=https://www.telegraph.co.uk/books/what-to-read/the-late-harper-lee-and-five-other-reclusive-authors/ |location=London}}</ref> \n| 1933\n| \n| American novelist, playwright and screenwriter\n|-\n| [[:it:Pordenone Montanari|Pordenone Montanari]]<ref>{{cite news|last=Alberge|first=Dalya|title=Italian recluse Pordenone Montanari, aged 73, hailed as a genius of art|url=https://www.theguardian.com/artanddesign/2010/aug/15/pordenone-montanari-artist-recluse-discovered|accessdate=15 August 2010|newspaper=Guardian Observer}}</ref><ref>{{cite news|last=Rees|first=Jasper|title=In old Italian home, new owner finds a secret master|url=http://www.thenational.ae/news/world/europe/in-old-italian-home-new-owner-finds-a-secret-master|accessdate=20 Janua